-- California Carbon Permits Sell for $11.48 at Auction
-- B y   L y n n   D o a n
-- 2013-11-22T20:11:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-22/california-carbon-permits-sell-for-11-48-at-auction.html
California sold all 16.6 million
carbon allowances put up for auction Nov. 19 at $11.48 each,
data posted on state Air Resources Board website show.
* State received 1.82 bids for every permit put up for sale.
Each allowance grants release of 1 metric ton of carbon as early
as this year
* State also sold out of allowances that can be used as early as
2016 for compliance, auctioning 9.56m at $11.10 each
* Link to auction results:  http://bit.ly/17At3yK 
* NOTE: 2013 allowances were expected to sell near “floor
price” of $10.71 each, Bloomberg New Energy Finance said in
Oct. 31 report
* NOTE: Allowances sold as part of cap-and-trade program
established by state last year in effort to cut greenhouse-gas
emissions to 1990 levels by 2020. For North America emissions
markets prices: EMUS<GO>  To contact the reporter on this story:
